HEADWORD: Androphore
<hw>An"dro*phore</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧n"dr⟦osl⟧*f⟦omac⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>'anh`r</grk>, <grk>'andro`s</grk>, man +
<grk>fe`rein</grk> to bear.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
support or column on which stamens are raised.</def>
<rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The part which in some
Siphonophora bears the male gonophores.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Andropogon</ent>⟦br⟧
